FBIS4-46172 "jptot022__l94081" JPRS-TOT-94-022-L JPRS Terrorism FOUO 27 May 1994 CENTRAL EURASIA MOLDOVA Dniester Procurator Injured in Assassination Attempt Dniester Procurator Injured in Assassination Attempt `Radio-Controlled' Device Used LD2705111194 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1001 GMT 27 May 94 LD2705111194 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service Russian BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Valeriy Demidetskiy] [Text] Kishinev [Chisinau], 27 May -- An assassination attempt has been made on Boris Luchik, the procurator of the Dniester Republic. Yesterday evening, when he and his wife entered their house accompanied by guards, a powerful explosion was heard near the lift. The procurator's wife perished, doctors are struggling to save the lives of Boris Luchik and his guards. It was reported to the ITAR-TASS correspondent today by Oleg Gudym, acting minister of state security of the Dniester Republic, that the explosion was carried out with the help of a radio-controlled device.
